cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a new method for mapping temporal variables into the NeuCube spiking neural network architecture for improved pattern recognition, predictive modeling, and understanding of stream data. This work involves machine learning techniques, spiking neural networks, and data visualization, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since the focus of the paper is on spiking neural networks and their application to temporal stream data, cs.NE is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The other two sub-categories, cs.SD and cs.CV, are less likely but still relevant due to the potential applications of the proposed method in sound and music processing and computer vision.
